description.narrative: MOE increased its capacity to establish;efficient management mechanisms. Under UNICEF&39;s leadership, the EiE Cluster supported the education sector response plan, mobilising resources for curriculum, training, materials, protocols, infrastructure, school meals and digital learning. UNICEF helped define the school feeding mechanism during the pandemic for nearly three million children. UNICEF organized cluster members aiming for the alignment of their actions towards the education sector plan and emergency response plan. UNICEF advocacy highlighted ECD, OOSC&A and school meals resulting in an increased budget for school feeding and the inclusion toddlers and adolescents, and more resources for ECD and alternative education. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/01/2022
